  "text": "From this perspective, the second order change process that reflects \"relations between people, the norms that regulate such relations and the social practices that constitute them, and the ways in which groups and communities as well as institutions respond to external forces\" implicitly emphasises the mode of agency referred to above (emphasis added, [CITATION_1] Kippax et al., , p.1373 ).",
